main event: Brilliant white or pinkish object observed in clear sky, appeared to be a meteor sighting, moved rapidly, believed to be a meteor.
interesting points: The object was observed for 1-2 minutes from a ground-visual source.
The object was reported by an aviation source.
The Air Technical Intelligence Center agreed that the sighting was likely a fireball or the reentry of a space vehicle/missile.
A questionnaire was sent to the witness who reported seeing a cylindrical object executing right-angle turns.
The Air Force concluded that the sighting was not an Unidentified Flying Object.
sighted object: Brilliant white or pinkish object, possibly a cylindrical object
photographs: No photographs included in the report
